(II) “GRID–ENHANCING TECHNOLOGY” INCLUDES:
1. A SYSTEM THAT USES REAL–TIME OR FORECASTED
WEATHER AND OPERATING CONDITIONS TO DETERMINE THE TRANSFER CAPACITY
OF TRANSMISSION SYSTEMS;
2. TECHNOLOGY THAT MODULATES CIRCUIT
IMPEDANCE OR OTHER ELECTRICAL PROPERTIES TO REROUTE POWER FLOWS AND
RELIEVE CONGESTION; AND
3. SOFTWARE THAT IDENTIFIES SWITCHING
CONFIGURATIONS TO REROUTE ELECTRICITY AND ALLEVIATE TRANSMISSION
CONSTRAINTS.
